---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 4 — why a new Raft leader can't be missing a
 * committed entry (two majorities overlap in ≥1 voter).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as an .astro component because MDX's JSX
 * parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. This
 * figure references no shared arrowhead markers, so it carries no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Two majorities overlap. The committed entry is on a majority; the winning candidate needs a majority; the overlapping voter holds the entry and only votes for an up-to-date candidate."
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">WHY A NEW LEADER CAN'T BE MISSING A COMMITTED ENTRY</text
            >
            <!-- five nodes -->
            <g>
                <circle cx="90" cy="78" r="22" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
                ></circle><text
                    x="90"
                    y="82"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">S1✓</text
                >
                <circle cx="170" cy="78" r="22" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
                ></circle><text
                    x="170"
                    y="82"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">S2✓</text
                >
                <circle cx="250" cy="78" r="22" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="2"
                ></circle><text
                    x="250"
                    y="82"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#7a1f12">S3✓</text
                >
                <circle cx="330" cy="78" r="22" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></circle><text
                    x="330"
                    y="82"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11"
                    fill="#6b675f">S4</text
                >
                <circle cx="410" cy="78" r="22" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></circle><text
                    x="410"
                    y="82"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11"
                    fill="#6b675f">S5</text
                >
            </g>
            <!-- commit majority bracket -->
            <path d="M 64 112 L 64 124 L 276 124 L 276 112" fill="none" stroke="#2f5d3a"></path>
            <text x="170" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >committed entry sits on a MAJORITY (S1,S2,S3)</text
            >
            <!-- vote majority bracket -->
            <path d="M 224 48 L 224 36 L 436 36 L 436 48" fill="none" stroke="#7a1f12"></path>
            <text x="330" y="30" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a1f12"
                >candidate needs a MAJORITY of votes (S3,S4,S5)</text
            >
            <!-- overlap callout -->
            <line x1="250" y1="100" x2="250" y2="160" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            ></line>
            <rect x="150" y="162" width="300" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="182"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">two majorities OVERLAP in ≥ 1 node (S3)</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="198" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >S3 holds the committed entry &amp; only votes for an</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="211" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >at-least-as-up-to-date candidate → winner has the entry too</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        On <code>RequestVote</code>, a follower refuses unless the candidate's log is <em
            >at least as up-to-date</em
        > (compare last-entry term, then index). A candidate missing a committed entry can never assemble
        a majority.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
